ztmp/

# tom_ts2dart was removed as a submodule (its standalone repo lives at
# github.com/al-the-bear/tom_ts2dart). Some hosts still have a leftover
# checkout of that nested repo on disk; without this rule a reconcile `git add`
# keeps re-staging it as a phantom gitlink with no .gitmodules entry, which then
# breaks recursive submodule update fleet-wide ("No url found for submodule path
# tom_ts2dart"). Ignore the leftover working copy so it is never re-added.
tom_ts2dart/
